// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance HokuyoUST10LXLiDAR : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Hokuyo UST-10LX LiDAR providing raw point cloud data for object detection and tracking in the vehicle's proximity. Operates as part of the Physical Twin Entity's Data Pre-Processing FE."
    DTDFVocab:producedData RawLiDARPointCloudData
]

instance IntelRealSenseD435iDepthCamera : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Intel RealSense D435i Depth Camera capturing 3D environmental data for object state estimation. Integrated with the Physical Twin Entity's sensor suite."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CameraDepthData
]

instance VehicleStateSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Onboard sensors continuously monitoring ego vehicle's speed and steering angle. Part of the Physical Twin Entity's sensor infrastructure."
    DTDFVocab:producedData VehicleStateData
]

instance PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingModule : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Processes raw LiDAR data using DBSCAN clustering and Kalman filter (implemented in MATLAB/Simulink) to generate object tracks (state estimates: size, position, velocity). Operates in Physical Twin Entity's Data Pre-Processing FE."
    DTDFVocab:producedData ProcessedObjectTracks
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance RawLiDARPointCloudData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Raw point cloud data stream transmitted via ROS2 topics from Physical Twin Entity to Digital Twin Entity's Data Collection FE. Serialized using ROS2 message serialization."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom HokuyoUST10LXLiDAR
]

instance CameraDepthData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "3D depth data stream from Intel RealSense D435i transmitted via ROS2 topics to Digital Twin Entity's Data Collection FE. Aligned with compatible units through Data Translation FE."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom IntelRealSenseD435iDepthCamera
]

instance VehicleStateData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Ego vehicle state data (speed, steering angle) streamed via ROS2 topics to Digital Twin Entity's Data Collection FE. Converted to compatible units via Data Translation FE."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom VehicleStateSensor
]

instance ProcessedObjectTracks : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    base:desc "Object tracks generated by Point Cloud Clustering & Tracking module (DBSCAN + Kalman filter) forwarded to Digital Twin Entity's Data Collection FE via ROS2 topics."
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingModule
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance DBSCANClusteringModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "DBSCAN clustering algorithm used for segmenting raw LiDAR point clouds into object clusters. Implemented in MATLAB/Simulink within Physical Twin Entity."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance KalmanFilterTrackingModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Kalman filter implementation for state estimation of detected objects (position, velocity, size). Operates in conjunction with DBSCAN in Physical Twin Entity."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance ACCControlStrategyModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Adaptive Cruise Control system implementing ISO 15622 (Sec 6.1-6.2) for performance class I (no road curvature). Offloaded computation from Physical Twin to Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ACCComputationEnabler
]

instance RawLiDARPointCloudDataStream : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time stream of raw LiDAR point clouds from Hokuyo UST-10LX. Used as input for object detection and tracking models."
    DTDFVocab:fromData RawLiDARPointCloudData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance CameraDepthDataStream : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time 3D depth data from Intel RealSense D435i. Used for environmental state estimation and object detection."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CameraDepthData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance VehicleStateDataStream : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Continuous stream of ego vehicle state (speed, steering angle) with timestamp synchronization. Used for ACC computation and system monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:fromData VehicleStateData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ACCComputationEnabler, DataStorageEnabler
]

instance ProcessedObjectTracksData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed object tracks containing state estimates (position, velocity, size) with temporal consistency. Used for ACC decision making and visualization."
    DTDFVocab:fromData ProcessedObjectTracks
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ACCComputationEnabler, RealTimeVisualizationEnabler
]

instance StoredVehicleData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Historical time-series data of vehicle state and object tracks stored in SQL database. Used for post-analysis and troubleshooting."
    DTDFVocab:fromData VehicleStateDataStream, ProcessedObjectTracksData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ReportingService
]

// C11: Enablers
instance ROS2Middleware : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Robot Operating System 2 (ROS2) providing inter-component communication, message serialization, and topic-based data transmission between Physical Twin and Digital Twin entities."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataCollectionService, DataTranslationService, ActuationService
]

instance NVIDIAJetpack5_0SDK : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "NVIDIA Jetpack 5.0 SDK for Jetson hardware programming and ROS2 integration on Physical Twin's NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano."
    DTDFVocab:enables PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance Python3_8 : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Python 3.8 used for rapid prototyping of ROS2 nodes and data processing pipelines in both Physical and Digital Twin entities."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataTranslationService
]

instance CPlusPlus : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "C++ used for implementing ROS2 node lifecycles and performance-critical components in both entities."
    DTDFVocab:enables ACCComputationEnabler, ActuationService
]

instance MATLABSimulink : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MATLAB/Simulink used for implementing complex algorithms (DBSCAN, Kalman filter) and simulation models."
    DTDFVocab:enables PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance DBSCANAlgorithm : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Density-Based Spatial Clustering of Applications with Noise (DBSCAN) algorithm for point cloud segmentation."
    DTDFVocab:enables PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance KalmanFilterImplementation : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Kalman filter implementation for state estimation of tracked objects with process and measurement noise modeling."
    DTDFVocab:enables PointCloudProcessingEnabler
]

instance SQLDatabase : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "SQL database for storing real-time vehicle state and object track data with timestamp indexing for post-analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataStorageEnabler
]

instance WiFiNetwork : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Wi-Fi network providing inter-entity communication with maximum end-to-end latency of 100 ms (per 3GPP TS 22.185)."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataCollectionService, ActuationService
]

instance PointCloudProcessingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Enabler combining DBSCAN clustering and Kalman filter tracking for processing raw LiDAR data into object tracks."
    DTDFVocab:enables ObjectTrackingService
]

instance ACCComputationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Computational enabler implementing ISO 15622 ACC control strategy with lead vehicle detection and speed computation."
    DTDFVocab:enables AdaptiveCruiseControlService
]

instance DataTranslationService : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Data translation layer serializing all data streams to ROS2 message types and converting units for inter-entity compatibility."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataCollectionService
]

instance DataStorageEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Data storage interface writing vehicle state and object tracks to SQL database with timestamp synchronization."
    DTDFVocab:enables ReportingService
]

instance RealTimeVisualizationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "3D CAD-like rendering engine for real-time visualization of ego vehicle state, object tracks, and projected path."
    DTDFVocab:enables RealTimeMonitoringService
]

// C6: Services
instance DataCollectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service collecting real-time data streams (LiDAR, camera, vehicle state) from Physical Twin via ROS2 topics and forwarding to Digital Twin's processing components."
    DTDFVocab:provides RealTimeDataCollectionInsight
]

instance ObjectTrackingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service processing raw sensor data through DBSCAN clustering and Kalman filtering to generate consistent object tracks."
    DTDFVocab:provides ObjectTrackConsistencyInsight
]

instance AdaptiveCruiseControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service implementing ACC logic (ISO 15622 class I) with lead vehicle detection and speed computation, offloaded from Physical Twin to Digital Twin."
    DTDFVocab:provides ACCPerformanceInsight, EmergencyBrakingAction, SpeedAdjustmentAction
]

instance RealTimeMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing 3D visualization of ego vehicle state, object tracks, and projected driving path for operator assessment of ACC performance."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemStateVisualizationInsight
]

instance RemoteManagementService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service enabling users to enable/disable ACC, adjust desired speed, and trigger emergency braking via control panel interface."
    DTDFVocab:provides ACCControlAction, EmergencyBrakingAction, SpeedAdjustmentAction
]

instance ReportingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service generating human-readable time-series reports of vehicle state and object tracks from stored SQL database data."
    DTDFVocab:provides PostAnalysisReportInsight
]

instance ActuationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service translating Digital Twin commands into physical actuation signals for vehicle speed control and steering via Physical Twin's actuation components."
    DTDFVocab:provides VehicleControlAction
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance RealTimeDataCollectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing confirmation of successful data collection from all Physical Twin sensors with timestamp synchronization."
]

instance ObjectTrackConsistencyInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight verifying temporal consistency of object tracks across sensor modalities with Kalman filter state estimates."
]

instance ACCPerformanceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight assessing ACC performance metrics (following distance, speed adaptation) based on real-time object tracking and vehicle state."
]

instance SystemStateVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight providing 3D visualization of ego vehicle state, surrounding object tracks, and projected driving path for operator assessment."
]

instance PostAnalysisReportInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Insight containing time-series reports of vehicle state and object tracks for post-incident analysis and troubleshooting."
]

instance ACCControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action enabling/disabling the Adaptive Cruise Control system based on operator input."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance EmergencyBrakingAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action triggering immediate emergency braking when collision risk is detected by the ACC system."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance SpeedAdjustmentAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action adjusting the desired speed of the ego vehicle based on operator input or ACC system recommendations."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic false
]

instance VehicleControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Action converting Digital Twin commands into physical actuation signals for vehicle speed and steering control."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C2: Acting Components
instance VedderElectronicSpeedController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Electronic Speed Controller converting voltage commands from Digital Twin into physical motor movement for the Traxxas Slash 4x4 vehicle."
]

instance SteeringServoActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Servo mechanism controlling the vehicle's steering angle based on commands from Digital Twin's Actuation FE."
]

// C1: Environments/Components
instance PhysicalTwinEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Physical Twin Entity representing the 1/10-scale autonomous vehicle's resources including sensors, actuators, and onboard compute (NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano). Custom addition to ISO 23247 architecture."
    base:contains HokuyoUST10LXLiDAR, IntelRealSenseD435iDepthCamera, VehicleStateSensor,
                 PointCloudClusteringAndTrackingModule, VedderElectronicSpeedController,
                 SteeringServoActuator
]

instance DigitalTwinEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Digital Twin Entity hosting core DT functionality including data collection, ACC computation, reporting, and actuation command generation. Implemented on external compute hardware."
    base:contains DataCollectionService, ObjectTrackingService, AdaptiveCruiseControlService,
                 RealTimeMonitoringService, RemoteManagementService, ReportingService,
                 ActuationService
]

instance UserEntity : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "User Entity providing unified interfaces (3D Visualization + Control Panel) for operators and developers. Implemented on separate hardware."
    base:contains RealTimeVisualizationEnabler, RemoteManagementService
]

instance TraxxasSlash4x4Vehicle : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "1/10-scale autonomous vehicle platform retrofitted with two-layer chassis architecture (lower level for steering/speed control, upper level for autonomy components)."
    base:contains PhysicalTwinEntity
]

instance ExternalComputeEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "External compute hardware hosting Digital Twin Entity components with low-latency Wi-Fi connection to Physical Twin."
    base:contains DigitalTwinEntity
]

instance ControlPanelUI : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Separate interface hardware providing 3D visualization and control panel for operator interaction with the Digital Twin system."
    base:contains UserEntity
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The digital twin (DT) interacts with the physical twin (PT) through the following outputs: **1) Desired speed commands**: Computed by the **ACC Controlling FE** in the Digital Twin Entity, sent to the **Actuation FE** in the Physical Twin Entity, and converted into motor voltage commands via the **Vedder Electronic Speed Controller**. **2) Emergency braking commands**: Triggered remotely via the **Control Panel** (User Entity) and transmitted to the **Actuation FE**. **3) Remote management signals**: Enable/disable ACC and modify desired speed, sent via the **User Interface FE** to the **Controlling FE**. **4) Data synchronization**: Clock synchronization between PT and DT is maintained with an accuracy of **100 ms** (due to hardware limitations) to ensure event ordering and coordination."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The digital twin operates at **real-time scales** with the following constraints: **1) Perception cycle**: Object tracks and vehicle state are updated continuously at rates sufficient for ACC (no explicit frequency specified but aligned with sensor refresh rates). **2) End-to-end latency**: **≤100 ms** for data transmission from PT to DT and vice versa (per **3GPP TS 22.185**). **3) Clock synchronization**: Devices must share a time reference with **100 ms accuracy** (due to hardware limitations). **4) Computation offloading**: The ACC system’s control loop runs on the DT, with actuation commands sent back to the PT in real-time. The system is designed for **low-latency, high-fidelity synchronization** between virtual and physical domains."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The digital twin constellation consists of the following orchestrated components: **1) Physical Twin Entity**: Hosts **sensors (LiDAR, camera)**, **actuators (motor, steering servo)**, and **pre-processing modules** (point cloud clustering/tracking). **2) Digital Twin Entity**: Implements **data collection**, **ACC computation**, **reporting**, and **data storage** (SQL). **3) User Entity**: Provides **3D Visualization** (real-time UI) and **Control Panel** (remote management). **4) Cross-System Entity**: **Data Translation FE** ensures interoperability between entities. The constellation follows an **entity-based structure** (per ISO 23247) but introduces the **Physical Twin Entity** to reflect the PT’s resources. Components communicate via **ROS2 topics** (intra-entity) and **Wi-Fi** (inter-entity) with **≤100 ms latency**."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The digital twin (DT) is primarily used during the **operation phase** of the vehicle’s lifecycle, with secondary applications in **development and validation**. **1) Operation Phase**: Enables **real-time monitoring**, **remote management**, and **predictive maintenance** of the ACC system. **2) Development Phase**: Serves as a **cyber-physical experimentation facility** for testing ACC algorithms (e.g., lead vehicle detection, speed control) in a **1/10-scale prototype**. **3) Validation Phase**: Used to **validate compliance** with **ISO 15622** (ACC performance class I) and ensure **safety-critical requirements** (e.g., latency, clock sync). The DT represents the PT **as operated**, not as designed or manufactured, focusing on **runtime behavior** and **dynamic interactions**."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Fidelity and validity are ensured through: **1) High-Fidelity Sensor Data**: Raw LiDAR and camera inputs are processed via **DBSCAN + Kalman filter** to generate accurate object tracks. **2) Real-Time Synchronization**: **≤100 ms latency** and **100 ms clock accuracy** ensure temporal alignment between PT and DT. **3) Validation Against Standards**: ACC functionality adheres to **ISO 15622 (performance class I)**. **4) Verification Mechanisms**: **ROS2** ensures modular testing, while **SQL storage** enables post-hoc validation of data integrity. **5) Uncertainty Management**: No explicit uncertainty quantification is mentioned, but **Kalman filtering** inherently accounts for sensor noise. **6) Error Handling**: Emergency braking commands provide a safety fallback for critical failures. The DT’s fidelity is constrained by **hardware limitations** (e.g., 100 ms clock sync) but meets **safety-critical requirements** for ACC."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The technical connection between the physical twin (PT) and digital twin (DT) includes: **1) Network Protocol**: **Wi-Fi** for inter-entity communication with **≤100 ms end-to-end latency** (per **3GPP TS 22.185**). **2) Intra-Entity Communication**: **ROS2 topics** for message passing between software components within the same entity. **3) Data Translation**: **Data Translation FE** serializes data, aligns message types, and performs unit conversions (e.g., voltage commands for actuation). **4) Clock Synchronization**: Devices share a time reference with **100 ms accuracy** (due to hardware constraints). **5) Hardware Deployment**: PT runs on **NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano**, DT on **external compute**, and UI on a **separate interface**."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The digital twin (DT) is hosted and deployed as follows: **1) Physical Twin (PT)**: Runs on a **1/10-scale autonomous vehicle** with **NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano** (primary compute) and **Jetson NX antenna**. **2) Digital Twin Entity**: Deployed on **external compute hardware** (not specified) to offload ACC computation from the PT. **3) User Entity**: Hosted on a **separate interface** (e.g., desktop/laptop) for **3D Visualization** and **Control Panel**. **4) Data Storage**: External **SQL database** for persistent storage of vehicle state and object tracks. **5) Middleware**: **ROS2** manages inter-component communication, while **Wi-Fi** handles inter-entity networking. The deployment follows a **distributed architecture** with clear separation of concerns."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "Horizontal integration is limited to the following external systems: **1) ROS2 Ecosystem**: Leverages **ROS2 nodes** and **topics** for interoperability with other ROS2-based systems (e.g., sensor drivers, simulation tools). **2) MATLAB/Simulink**: Used for complex algorithms (e.g., point cloud processing) and can integrate with other **Simulink-based tools**. **3) SQL Database**: Stores data in a format compatible with **standard database tools** for analysis. **4) No explicit integration** with external DTs or enterprise systems is mentioned. The DT focuses on **internal consistency** (PT-DT-UI) rather than broader horizontal integration."
]

instance data_ownership_and_privacy : DTDFVocab:DataOwnershipPrivacy [
    base:desc "Data ownership and privacy considerations are not explicitly addressed in the document. The following assumptions can be inferred: **1) Data Ownership**: Likely owned by the **vehicle operator/developer** (as the DT is used for **development and remote management**). **2) Privacy**: No mention of **data anonymization**, **access controls**, or **compliance with regulations** (e.g., GDPR). **3) Storage**: Data is stored in an **external SQL database**, but no encryption or access policies are specified. **Not in Document** for detailed ethical/technical aspects."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The digital twin (DT) adheres to the following standards: **1) Architectural Standard**: **ISO 23247 (Part 2)** for the **reference architecture**, with adaptations (e.g., **Physical Twin Entity**, split **User Interface FE**). **2) ACC Standard**: **ISO 15622** for **performance class I** (basic control strategy). **3) Communication Standard**: **3GPP TS 22.185** for **≤100 ms latency** in V2V communication. **4) Middleware**: **ROS2** (no specific standard, but widely adopted in robotics). **5) Sensor Protocols**: **OPC UA** is mentioned as a potential implementation for **Data Translation FE** (though not used in this case). The DT follows a **standardized yet domain-adapted** approach, balancing **ISO 23247** with automotive-specific requirements."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "Security and safety are addressed through the following measures: **1) Safety-Critical Requirements**: **≤100 ms latency** and **100 ms clock sync** ensure real-time coordination for ACC. **2) Emergency Braking**: Provides a **safety fallback** for critical failures. **3) Remote Management**: Enables **geographically distributed operation** but lacks explicit **fail-safe mechanisms** for remote commands. **4) No explicit cybersecurity measures** (e.g., encryption, authentication) are mentioned for data transmission or storage. **5) Hardware Limitations**: **100 ms clock accuracy** may impact safety in stricter applications (e.g., full autonomy). The DT is classified as a **Fully Autonomous Digital Twin with Human-in-the-Loop** (per **David and Bork’s taxonomy**), implying **human oversight** for critical decisions."
]